symfony.title: Getting Started with Symfony
symfony.description: Symfony is an open-source PHP framework used for developing web applications. It provides a robust structure, powerful tools, and reusable components to make development faster, cleaner, and more maintainable.

apiPlatform.title: Boost your website with Api-platform
apiPlatform.description: API Platform is a PHP framework based on Symfony that allows you to quickly create APIs (REST, GraphQL, etc.). It automatically generates an API from your entities (data models), while respecting web standards.

react.title: Boost your application with React
react.description: React is a JavaScript framework (technically a library) used to build interactive user interfaces, especially for fast, dynamic web applications. It works with reusable components and intelligently updates the display without reloading the entire page.

flutter.title: Build Cross-Platform Apps with Flutter
flutter.description: Flutter is an open-source framework created by Google for developing mobile, web, and desktop applications with a single codebase. It uses the Dart language and allows you to create very fast and beautiful apps with smooth animations.
